    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Instruments designed to demonstrate the mothion of rotating bodies, consisting essentially of a rotating wheel mounted in a ring, with its axis free to turn in any direction. With modifications or in conjunction with other equipment, these may be used as navigational devices, or to stabilize ships and mono-rail vehicles.</Note_Text>
